The article is a press briefing by Secretary of Defense Robert Gates. He discusses the President's decision to withdraw all U.S. forces from Iraq by the end of 2011, in accordance with the Status of Forces Agreement. Secretary Gates explains that the decision was made after a thorough and deliberative process, taking into account the views of military commanders and the risks involved. He also mentions the possibility of a small training and support presence remaining in Iraq beyond 2011, but emphasizes that no such request has been made by the Iraqis at this time. Additionally, Secretary Gates addresses questions about troop levels in Afghanistan and the shift in focus to combating al Qaeda in Afghanistan and Pakistan. He states that the ultimate size and duration of the forces in Afghanistan will be determined by an ongoing review and the President's decisions.